We recommended that Management:
Instruct the Municipal Accountant to make the necessary adjusting journal entries in the books of accounts;
Direct the Municipal Treasurer to transfer funds from the Trust Fund account to the General Fund bank account in the amount of ₱452,212.53;
Instruct the Municipal Accountant to record the receipt of share from the Lotto Charity Fund as income in the GF books using the account title “Share from PCSO”; and
Utilize the funds in the conduct of charity programs and activities which are consistent with the PCSO line-up of services under the Lotto Charity Fund to become more effective partner of the national government in the extension of services to the marginal sector in the community.

We recommended that Management:
Instruct the Municipal Accountant together with the concerned department or end-user to gather all the pertinent documents for the recognition of expense of non-existent inventories in the books of accounts;
Direct the GSO to monitor the distribution of supplies and materials held for distribution and ensure that complete documentation is prepared, with the assistance of the concerned department or end-user, for submission to the Accounting Office for proper recognition of expense in the books of accounts;
Require the GSO to conduct a physical count of all inventories semi-annually and a report thereon be prepared and submitted to the Audit Team;
Direct the Municipal Accountant to record all inventoriable supplies as inventories and recognize the same as expense upon issuance based on the SSMI duly supported with Requisition and Issue Slip; and
Require the GSO to consolidate weekly the RIS issued and facilitate the preparation of SSMI which shall be the basis of the Municipal Accountant in recording the issuances, consumption and/or distribution in the appropriate expense accounts.

We recommended that Management:
1. Require the GSO to render a Report on Local Road Network at the end of the accounting period, as well as maintain Local Road Network Property Cards for all roads and its components with complete details and description;
2. Require the GSO as head of the Inventory Committee to prepare the Report on the Physical Count of the Road Network System upon completion of the conduct of inventory of all local roads;
3. Require the Municipal Accountant to maintain Local Road Networks Ledger Card for all roads and its components, as well as individual subsidiary ledgers for each road component with complete details and description;
4. Require the Municipal Engineer to provide the Municipal Accountant and the GSO with the complete description and cost segregation of road components for all existing road projects; and
5. Require the Municipal Accountant to make proper disclosure of the total road network system in the Notes to the Financial Statements.

We recommended that
Management:
a) Strictly enforce the immediate settlement/liquidation of cash advances to accountable officials/employees who are still in the service and exhaust all possible means to collect the cash advances from previous employees who were no longer in the service, otherwise, proceed against the signatories of the clearance, who are still in the service;
b) Ensure that previous cash advances of accountable officers have been fully settled before granting additional cash advances; 
c) Ensure that cash advances are only granted to appointed/designated cash disbursing officers, in case of regular cash advances, while cash advances for special purpose are granted to official/employee of the LGU; and
d) Ensure that all officials and employees who have filed their retirement/resignation have fully settled/liquidated their cash advances before signing their clearances.

We recommended that
Management:
a. Instruct the Municipal Treasurer to refund the unutilized SAP-ESP fund amounting to ₱434,500.00;
b. Instruct the Municipal Accountant to submit a liquidation report of the SAP-ESP fund;
c. Instruct the MSWDO to submit to the Audit Team printed copy of the pictures of the beneficiaries during actual receipt of the assistance/stipend for completeness of supporting documents in the disbursement of public funds; and
d. Require the MSWDO to take the necessary actions to facilitate the refund of the subsidy by the ineligible beneficiaries.

