observations.recommendation:
We recommended that
Management:
a. designate an employee or official to conduct a pre-repair evaluation on all vehicles of the LGU subject for repair and prepare reports on the results of evaluation and inspection;
b. require the service provider to issue warranty certificate prior to issuance of Certificate of Acceptance and indicate the nature of service/s performed and accepted;
c. require the General Services Officer (GSO) to prepare the Waste Material Report; and
d. remind the Municipal Accountant of his duty to check the completeness of the supporting documents prior to payment.

We recommended that Management:

Require the GSO and OIC-Municipal Accountant to maintain Property Cards and Property, Plant and Equipment Ledger Cards (PPELC), respectively, and to record all properties that have been acquired and issued therein. The documents shall be the basis of the Inventory Committee in conducting the annual physical inventory count of properties;

Strictly implement the annual physical inventory taking by the Inventory Committee, and reconcile the result with the accounting and GSO records; and to prepare and submit the RPCPPE;

Direct the personnel concerned to reconstruct the available records in order to have the required property cards to arrive at a correct balance of the PPE account; and 

Require the GSO to identify the unserviceable properties, and prepare the necessary reports for disposal of the same and subsequently, in accordance with the requirements and procedures in the disposal of properties.

We recommended that Management adhere to the provisions prescribed by existing laws, rules and regulations in the grant and liquidation of cash advances, more specifically:

1.    “Strictly” enforce the immediate settlement/liquidation of cash advances of accountable officials/employees who are still in the service and exhaust all possible means to collect the cash advances from previous employees who are no longer in the service; otherwise, proceed against the signatories of the clearance, who are still in the service;

2.    Ensure that previous cash advances of accountable officers have been fully settled before granting additional cash advances;


3.    Ensure that cash advances shall only be granted to appointed/designated cash disbursing officers, in case of regular cash advances, while cash advances for special purpose shall be granted to an organic official/employee of the LGU;


4.    Ensure that all officials and employees who have filed their retirement/resignation have fully settled/liquidated their cash advances before signing of their clearances; and those receivable which could no longer be settled, the agency may request for write-off in accordance with the guidelines and procedures provided under COA Circular No. 2016-005, dated December 19, 2016.

